This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a novel framework to improve active learning by reducing the number of human interactions required to train deep neural networks. The paper also uses image datasets such as CIFAR-10 and EuroSAT, which suggests that it may also belong to computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves human annotation, which is a common theme in natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses clustering techniques, which are commonly used in data science (cs.DS) sub-category.
